    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-07-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-07-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="412" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d412">
                <head>
                    <seg type="margin">[92]</seg> *<hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Field</persName>, Acting Attorney-General, to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Barlow</persName>, United States
                                    marshal.</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>,
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-07-03">
                        <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 3, 1869</date>.</dateline>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis C. Barlow</hi>, <hi rend="italic">United States Marshal, New York:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The officers and men must be put in judicial custody as soon as
                                possible, either under separate or joint complaints j and if a writ
                                of <hi rend="italic">habeas corpus</hi> issues before they are
                                arrested on a warrant, pending the hearing of the writ, a warrant
                                can be obtained, and immediately served, if they are discharged at
                                the hearing.</p>
                <p>Give copy to district attorney.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. A. FIELD,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting-Attorney
                                        General.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
